cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use this software, please cite it using the metadata below."
title: "Murmuration — 3D Bird Flock Simulation"
abstract: >
  A Python simulation of starling murmurations in a full 3D volume,
  implementing two runtime-switchable flocking models — the hybrid projection
  model from Pearce et al. (2014, PNAS), with true 3D spherical-cap occlusion
  and a boundary-seeking projection direction, and topological Reynolds boids.
  It provides GPU-accelerated instanced rendering via ModernGL and standalone,
  unit-tested science modules grounded in three papers: Pearce et al. (2014)
  occlusion, opacity Θ/Θ', density scaling and correlation time; Young et al.
  (2013) consensus robustness and cost-optimal neighbour count m*; and
  Goodenough et al. (2017) ecological dynamics (seasonal size, critical mass,
  predator flight response, roosting, day-length). Includes eight scenario
  presets, real-time metrics (order parameter α, internal/external opacity,
  angular momentum, dispersion), a Docker pipeline, and a unit-test suite.
